org.beryx.streamplify

Interface IntArraySupplier

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CartesianProductSupplier, CartesianProductSupplier.BigInt, CartesianProductSupplier.Long, CombinationSupplier, CombinationSupplier.BigInt, CombinationSupplier.Long, DerangementSupplier, DerangementSupplier.BigInt, DerangementSupplier.Long, PartialPermutationSupplier, PartialPermutationSupplier.BigInt, PartialPermutationSupplier.Long, PermutationSupplier, PermutationSupplier.BigInt, PermutationSupplier.Long, PowerSetSupplier, PowerSetSupplier.BigInt, PowerSetSupplier.Long

    public interface IntArraySupplier
    This interface acts as a trait that helps implementing the valueSupplier requested by indexed-spliterators (such as LongIndexedSpliterator or BigIntegerIndexedSpliterator) with the type parameter int[].
    There is an implicit assumption that the implementing class uses an index (or some similar information) in order to decide whether the value to be supplied can be computed based on the previous value or based on the index.

    • Method Detail

      • getCurrentSequence

        int[] getCurrentSequence()
        Returns:
        the current sequence provided by this value supplier

      • computeNext

        void computeNext()
        Computes the value to be supplied next, using the currently supplied value. The next call of getCurrentSequence() should return this newly computed value.

      • unrank

        int[] unrank()
        Returns:
        the next value to be supplied. It is assumed that the next value cannot be obtained using the current one, but it has to be computed based on an index (or some similar information) handled by the implementing class.

      • getNextSequence

        default int[] getNextSequence(boolean useNext)
        Retrieves the next value to be supplied. Postcondition: a call to getCurrentSequence() will return an equal (but not identical) value.
        Parameters:
        useNext - true, if the next value can be computed based on the current one;
        Returns:
        the next value to be supplied. This should not be a reference to the array that backs getCurrentSequence().
